channel.title: Please Help
channel.description:
Does anyone have any idea why this is happening everytime I try and connect to my own server.. No-Ip DUC Is running and anything else that should be..
As you can see by the screenshot.. Others can connect to the server...
[img]http://i167.photobucket.com/albums/u134/Scotticus22/whyisthishappening.jpg[/img]

item.title: Please Help
item.dc:creator: @n10si_t n10si t
item.description:
@n10si_t wrote:

You can’t connect to your own server using your server IP.

You have to use your default gateway.

To find this, go into the start menu and open the “cmd” program.

Type in “ipconfig”

and then at the top some where you should see something that says:

Default Gateway: 192.168.1.***

Read full topic

@silabgarza wrote:

in server.java look for

Checking Server Status...

after that you should see “s.close();”
comment out that line by chaning
s.close();
to
//s.close();
